The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                79-year-old widow who lived alone was throttled to death outside her Barasat home early on Tuesday. Those who attacked Bani Chowdhury took away the gold chain, bangles, rings and earrings she was wearing. Her daughter and help found her lying in a pool of blood at the back of her house. Neighbours had seen Chowdhury picking flowers during her morning walk.   Kidnap arrest: Chandan Dugar, a realtor, was arrested outside Howrah station on Tuesday for allegedly kidnapping 60-year-old Jyotsna Bal, who has been missing since September 4. Jyotsnas brother had complained that she was abducted after she refused to hand over her property in Hindustan Park to the realtor.  Man shot: Prakash Yadav, a 37-year-old contractor, was shot outside his in-laws Titagarh home on Tuesday evening. The two men who fired at him fled on a motorcycle. Yadav died at RG Kar hospital.  Life term: A fast-track court in Howrah on Tuesday sentenced Mangal Gayen, 40, to life imprisonment for killing his wife in October 2005. Gayen slit his wifes throat. Mangals mother has been acquitted.                                                                                                                                               
